docs.lead_paragraph: BUENOS AIRES, July 20. -- The Chaco war has given rise to a subsidiary conflict of widespread ramifications -- the war of the peacemakers. This subsidiary conflict got under way again this week on at least four fronts, with Buenos Aires, Rio de Janeiro, Lima and Bogota Foreign Offices competing for leadership.
